      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric between CFD predictions and experimental measurements must be defined and applied; mean absolute error must be within 15% for hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) computed for all five operating conditions. Mean absolute error between CFD predictions and experimental measurements is 6.3%. Maximum single-point deviation is 9.8%. All predictions satisfy RH < 1 acceptance criterion consistent with predicate device performance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
