      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be directly relevant to the hemolysis prediction decision for CPB device evaluation.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary regulatory QoI for CPB device hemolysis assessment. The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is also computed as a secondary QoI. Both quantities are directly linked to the clinical decision criterion and are standard metrics in FDA guidance for blood-contacting device evaluation."
    },
    {
